{
  "texts": [
    "The mapΦ Σ: C (Σ) → A(Σ)is a unitary isomorphism of A(∂Σ)-modules.The proof appears in Appendix A.Remark 3.6.",
    "There is a well-known description of Tube algebras in terms of χ and the adjoint of the forgetful functor F: Z(C) → C (see [33], and [46,47] for a nice overview in the context of Levin-Wen models).",
    "Following [34], we denote the adjunction F ⊣ Tr.",
    "ThenTube S ≃ End Z 1 (C) (Tr χ ⊗S),with the isomorphism provided by the adjunction once the vector space of the Tube algebra is realised as Tube S ≃ a∈Irr C C(a ⊗ χ ⊗S ⊗ a * → χ ⊗S).",
    "On Tube S -representations the adjunction gives the isomorphismsC(X → χ ⊗S) ≃ Z(C)(X → Tr χ ⊗S),where the right hand side is a natural representation of End Z(C) (Tr χ ⊗S) given by composition of morphisms."
  ]
}